The paper proposes a new technique for clustering and classifying time-series data using temporal logic formulae. This involves exploring the space of all possible Signal Temporal Logic (STL) formulas, which is a machine learning and artificial intelligence problem (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the application of this technique in cyber-physical systems, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of this technique in healthcare, which could involve security and privacy (cs.CR).
